======================================================================
PART 2: DEVIATION FROM 1/3
======================================================================

  1/3 - Var/Mean^2 = sum of level correction terms

  Actually: 1/3 - E2/E0 = 1/3 - 2(n-2)/(n(n-1))
    = [n(n-1) - 6(n-2)] / (3n(n-1))
    = [n^2-n-6n+12] / (3n(n-1))
    = [n^2-7n+12] / (3n(n-1))
    = [(n-3)(n-4)] / (3n(n-1))

  So: 1/3 - E2/E0 = (n-3)(n-4) / (3n(n-1))
    n=3: (n-3)(n-4)/(3n(n-1)) = 0, actual = 0, match = True
    n=4: (n-3)(n-4)/(3n(n-1)) = 0, actual = 0, match = True
    n=5: (n-3)(n-4)/(3n(n-1)) = 1/30, actual = 1/30, match = True
    n=6: (n-3)(n-4)/(3n(n-1)) = 1/15, actual = 1/15, match = True
    n=7: (n-3)(n-4)/(3n(n-1)) = 2/21, actual = 2/21, match = True
    n=8: (n-3)(n-4)/(3n(n-1)) = 5/42, actual = 5/42, match = True
    n=9: (n-3)(n-4)/(3n(n-1)) = 5/36, actual = 5/36, match = True

  For n=3,4: this is 0 (Var/Mean^2 = 1/3 exactly)
  For n>=5: level-4+ corrections bring it closer to 1/3 (but don't reach it)

  Deviation budget:
    n=5: E2=3/10, E4+=1/60, total=19/60, 1/3-total=1/60
    n=6: E2=4/15, E4+=1/45, total=13/45, 1/3-total=2/45
    n=7: E2=5/21, E4+=11/504, total=131/504, 1/3-total=37/504
    n=8: E2=3/14, E4+=5/252, total=59/252, 1/3-total=25/252
    n=9: E2=7/36, E4+=3163/181440, total=38443/181440, 1/3-total=22037/181440

