======================================================================
PART 6: FORBIDDEN VALUES AND FOURIER STRUCTURE
======================================================================

  n=7: Mean = 315/4 = 78.75
  Var = 206325/128 = 1611.91
  SD = 40.1486
  Z-score of H=63: 0.3923
  Z-score of H=7: 1.7871
  Z-score of H=21: 1.4384
  Z-score of H=189 (max): 2.7460

  The forbidden values are NOT extreme! They're near the bulk.
  The obstruction must be STRUCTURAL, not statistical.

  Level-2 analysis for H=63:
  Need level-2 sum = -(78.75 - 63) - (level 4+6 corrections) ~ -15.75
  Level-2 terms are +/-3.75
  Need ~50.4 out of 105 terms positive -> perfectly feasible
  The obstruction is NOT a magnitude constraint but a PARITY/LATTICE constraint

  Lattice analysis (multiply by 32):
  32H = 2520 + 120*S2 + 6*S4a + 12*S4b + S6
  where S2, S4a, S4b, S6 are sums of +/-1 variables
  32*63 = 2016 = 2016
  32*7 = 224 = 224
  32*21 = 672 = 672

  Mod 8 constraint: 6*S4a + 4*S4b + S6 = 0 mod 8
  (same for all H values)
  Mod 3: S6 = 0 mod 3 for all H
  Mod 7: S2 + 6*S4a + 5*S4b + S6 = 0 mod 7
  This constrains which H values are reachable mod 7!

======================================================================
PART 7: GCD AND LATTICE STRUCTURE OF H-SPECTRUM
======================================================================

  At n=7: GCD of H-spectrum = 16
  So 32H = 512h for odd h, meaning all reachable lattice points are 0 mod 512
  2520 mod 512 = 472
  Need: 120*S2 + 6*S4a + 12*S4b + S6 = 40 mod 512

  Re-checking: H(transitive T_7) = 1 (only path: 0->1->...->6)
  So GCD of H-spectrum at n=7 includes 1, hence GCD = 1
  The previous GCD=16 report may have been for a DIFFERENT quantity
  (perhaps the level-2 energy sublattice or coefficient denominators)

