======================================================================
PART 9: THE 'ALMOST 1/3' PHENOMENON
======================================================================

  Why V(3) = V(4) = 1/3:
    n=3: E2/E0 = 2*1/(3*2) = 1/3, only level
    n=4: E2/E0 = 2*2/(4*3) = 1/3, E4/E0 = 2*0^2/P(4,4) = 0
    n=5: E2/E0 = 3/10, E4/E0 = 1/60
    n=6: E2/E0 = 4/15, E4/E0 = 2*4/(6*5*4*3) = 8/360 = 1/45

